Male genitalia:
Median lobe consisting of a few sclerites, well separated apically (
Fig. 12A, B, C
). Shape of paramere narrowly triangular, with very dense, strong, long setae along dorsal margin (
Fig. 12D
).

The species is widely distributed in the northern half of Australia. Records are from north-western Australia (Kimberley region), Northern Territories and Queensland south to Brisbane and Stradbroke Island (
Fig. 22
).
